-	Angular.js is a library/web application framework for building client side web applications.

-	Node.js is a platform for building event-driven, non blocking server side applications.

-	Express.js is a framework built on top of node.js for building server side web applications.

Node is your server.
Express is a framework to make coding your server easier.
Angular is a framework that helps you organize your JavaScript on the front-end.

Angular.js => build awesome front-end of app.

Express.js => allows to develop web app back-end faster.

Node.js => allows to run Express.js on it :D
